(79, 'Netflix and Amazon score billion pound revenue in battle with UK broadcasters', '<div>Without a major British rival, TV and film fans are turning to the Silicon Valley giants</div>', '<div><br></div><div>Netflix and Amazon made £1.1bn in revenues from UK streaming customers in 2018, double the amounts the UK’s biggest broadcasters were able to make from their own streaming services. The figures have highlighted just how much the absence of a true British rival to the Silicon Valley giants is a missed opportunity.</div><div><br></div><div>Netflix is estimated to have made £693m in revenues from its 10 million UK subscribers last year, while rival Amazon notched up £400m from an estimated 7.7 million subscribers to its Prime Video service, according to research from media regulator Ofcom.</div><div><br></div><div>The streaming services of the UK’s main commercial broadcasters – ITV Hub, Channel 4’s All 4, Channel 5’s My5 and Sky’s Now TV – made about £530m last year.</div><div><br></div><div><header class=\"header\" style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Guardian Text Sans Web&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\"><div class=\"headline\" style=\"color: black; font-size: 18px; font-family: &quot;GH Guardian Headline&quot;, Georgia, serif; line-height: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;\"><span data-offset-key=\"1idvg-0-0\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Seven services dominate the UK video on-demand market</span></div><div class=\"standfirst\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Guardian Text Egyptian Web&quot;, Georgia, serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin-top: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px;\"><span data-offset-key=\"foaal-0-0\">Monthly users, millions*</span></div></header><div data-id=\"bar\" data-res-y=\"false\" class=\"chart js-chart\" style=\"position: relative; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: &quot;Guardian Text Sans Web&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, &quot;Lucida Grande&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; marg